title: AWS RDS: Connections
agents: aws
catalog: cloud/aws
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the number of database connections in use.

 To make this check work you have to configure the related
 special agent {Amazon Web Services (AWS)}.

 No default levels are set. Upper levels are configurable via the
 rule "AWS/RDS Connections".

item:
 Name of the instance and region name (to avoid duplicate services
 in case of multi-region monitoring).

discovery:
 One service is create for each database if all required metrics
 (DatabaseConnections) are given.
